Hi , and hello and merry christmas to you all!!! .I was wondering today that when christianity was introduced to japan did any daimyo/ or current shogun send any envoys to the pope.Im sure that there is some vague record of japanese retainers attending the vatican , so does anybody know anything similiar. Also im curious when the first samurai sword was brought to europe and how it was recieved. Merry christmas all , as ever i enjoy all your help and suggestions. p.s You all should read ashida kims website, i laughed so much ( buy a balaclava and you too could be a mystic ninja !!!)       james
